subjects in the final hundred verses of the canto, see Hollander ("Dante's 'Georgic' [}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Inferno}{\plain \fs24 \f1  \softline
XXIV, 1-18]," }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Dante Studies}{\plain \fs24 \f1  102 [1984]), p. 114:\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab \tab 46-78:   the barren landscape of this scene (}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 rura}{\plain \fs24 \f1 )\par
