ed il rapporto fra Dante e Virgilio nell'Antepurgatorio," in }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1\lang1040 Studi Americani su Dante}{\plain \fs24 \f1\lang1040 , ed. G. C. \softline
Alessio and R. Hollander [Milan: F. Angeli, 1989], pp. 122-24), another example of his not \softline
understanding his own limitations.  His epigrammatic concluding utterance, though taken }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 in bono}{\plain \fs24 \f1  \softline
by commentator after commentator (and perhaps most pleasingly in the commentary of \softline
Benvenuto [to these verses], who goes on to claim that Dante himself was most prudent in using \softline
