detached from the place they have left, they are on the right road yet cannot move; not quite sure \softline
where they are headed, they are poised between memory and anticipation.'\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 94-96.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   For Dante's shadow, see the note to }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Purgatorio}{\plain \fs24 \f1  III.16-18.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 101-102.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   The saved souls now express their concern: Dante and Virgil are heading in the \softline
wrong direction (see Margherita Frankel, "La similitudine della zara (}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1\lang1040 Purg}{\plain \fs24 \f1\lang1040 . VI, 1-12) ed il \softline
rapporto fra Dante e Virgilio nell'Antepurgatorio," in }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1\lang1040 Studi Americani su Dante}{\plain \fs24 \f1\lang1040 , ed. G. C. Alessio \softline
and R. Hollander [Milan: F. Angeli, 1989], pp. 121-22).  They are thus aesthetically and morally \softline
disturbing as newcomers to purgatory.  They seem obviously entitled to be present but somehow \softline
