}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab The gesture that they make is puzzling to American readers, who give the sign for 'stop!' \softline
or 'go back!' by extending their palms outward.  As Lombardi (comm. to verse 102) calmly points \softline
out, 'The gesture referred to here by the poet is exactly the one with which we signal to others \softline
