God's presence (at least not in Dante's mind), but he surely did have some kind of access to the \softline
Scripture, although he evidently -- at least in Dante's eyes -- understood it poorly.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 130.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   In the wake Tommaseo (comm. to vv. 130-132) many modern commentators \softline
suggest that there is a reference here to Virgil's Palinurus (}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Aen}{\plain \fs24 \f1 . VI.362): 'Nunc me fluctus habet \softline
